In my Angular floating-persona-btn component, the persona label text inside 
the circular ring button is breaking mid-word — e.g. "Associate" renders as 
"Associat" on one line and "e" on the next. I need the full role name to fit 
on a single line inside the ring at ALL browser zoom levels (50%–150%) and 
all viewport widths.

Root causes to address (I've diagnosed these — please fix all of them, don't 
just patch one):

1. WORD BREAKING: The label wraps mid-word. `white-space: nowrap` alone is 
   NOT enough because a separate word-break mechanism is splitting the word. 
   Add `word-break: keep-all` and `overflow-wrap: normal` to the label so a 
   single word can never be split across lines. Also remove any `max-width` 
   constraint on the label element — a max-width narrower than the word 
   forces the break.

2. MEDIA QUERY OVERRIDES: The component has `@media (max-width: 1280px)` and 
   `@media (max-width: 768px)` blocks that each redefine 
   `.persona-label-role` font-size (e.g. 0.72rem). Browser zoom changes the 
   effective CSS viewport width (e.g. 150% zoom on a 1920px screen = 1280 
   CSS px), so these media queries silently activate at certain zoom levels 
   and override the base font-size. You MUST apply the single-line rules 
   (white-space: nowrap, word-break: keep-all) AND an appropriately small 
   font-size INSIDE every media query block too — not just the base rule — 
   otherwise the fix disappears at those zoom levels.

3. CIRCLE SIZE: If the longest role name ("HR Partner", 10 chars) still 
   can't fit on one line at a readable font size, increase the ring size to 
   accommodate it. The structure is: .persona-float (outer container) 
   contains an SVG .ring-svg (viewBox 0 0 120 120, scales automatically via 
   width/height 100%) and an .inner-circle div where the label sits. 
   Increase .persona-float and .inner-circle dimensions proportionally 
   across the base rule AND each media query so the text always fits. The 
   SVG needs no viewBox change since it scales with its container.

Requirements for the fix:
- The longest persona name must fit on ONE line inside the ring at 50%, 67%, 
  100%, 125%, and 150% zoom.
- Font size should stay as large as possible while still fitting — don't 
  shrink it more than necessary.
- Give me the corrected .scss with the base rule and ALL media query blocks 
  updated consistently.
- Add a brief comment explaining that word-break: keep-all (not just 
  white-space: nowrap) is what prevents mid-word splitting, and that the 
  media query blocks must be kept in sync because zoom activates them.

The persona names are: "Associate" (9 chars), "Manager" (7 chars), 
